On MacOS, we use clang. Your build seems to be using GCC.
We have not tested these builds and it is possible these are broken.
However, these log lines give me the impression that you are running into a compiler bug:

gcc: internal compiler error: Killed (program cc1plus)
Please submit a full bug report,
with preprocessed source if appropriate.

These lines are emitted by GCC, so I recommend reaching out to GCC developers.

body:
On MacOS, we use clang. Your build seems to be using GCC.
We have not tested these builds and it is possible these are broken.
However, these log lines give me the impression that you are running into a compiler bug:

```
gcc: internal compiler error: Killed (program cc1plus)
Please submit a full bug report,
with preprocessed source if appropriate.
```

These lines are emitted by GCC, so I recommend reaching out to GCC developers.
